**single-file API gateway** to support full **CRUD operations** (Create, Read, Update, Delete) 

We’ll keep it:

* Simple (single file)
* Realistic (API style)
* Ready to plug Redis later (currently in-memory map)

---

# APIs You’ll Get

| Method | Endpoint          | Description  |
| ------ | ----------------- | ------------ |
| POST   | `/api/order`      | Create order |
| GET    | `/api/order?id=1` | Read one     |
| GET    | `/api/orders`     | Read all     |
| PUT    | `/api/order?id=1` | Update       |
| DELETE | `/api/order?id=1` | Delete       |

---

# Test All CRUD

## Create

curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/order \
-H "Content-Type: application/json" \
-d '{"symbol":"AAPL","qty":10}'

---

## Read One

curl "http://localhost:8080/api/order?id=1"

---

## Read All

curl http://localhost:8080/api/orders

---

## Update

curl -X PUT "http://localhost:8080/api/order?id=1" \
-d '{"symbol":"AAPL","qty":50}'

---

## Delete

curl -X DELETE "http://localhost:8080/api/order?id=1"

---

# Next Level (Important)

Right now:
    Data is in memory (lost on restart)

Upgrade path:

* Replace `OrderStore` with Redis:

  * `SET order:1 {...}`
  * `GET order:1`
  * `DEL order:1`

